he family of a Marine helicopter co-pilot who died in a1983 crash in the Atlantic Ocean near Virginia Beach, Va.   The dissenting justices denounced the ruling as a``breathtakingly'' far-reaching grant of immunity to the nation'sdefense industry.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Boeing Co. warned Aloha Airlines last fallthat unless serious corrosion on its oldest aircraft was fixedthrough a stepped-up repair program the planes might become unsafe,documents show.   Nevertheless, according to documents released Monday, Aloha inearly March canceled plans for the speedier maintenance schedule,less than seven weeks before one of its aging Boeing 737s brokeapart during flight on April 18.   The documents were released by the National TransportationSafety Board, which is investigating the accident.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The crash of an Airbus A320 jetliner during ademonstration flight in France could make potential purchasers ofthe plane wary and may be damaging for its manufacturer, someairline analysts say.   Sunday's crash of the ultra-modern Air France jet could inflict``psychological'' damage on the highly touted A320 and promptcancelled orders and lost sales. The incident also focusesattention on the trend toward more technology and fewer pilots,analysts said Monday.</TEXT><NOTE>MORE</NOTE></DOC>